-- Peruvian Stocks: Austral, Casa Grande, Grana, Telefonica
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-03-27T21:34:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/peru-stocks-austral-buenaventura-candente-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 3:10 p.m. local time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for a third session, adding 1.4
percent to 23,650.62. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed 0.7
percent to 2,954.77.  Casa Grande (CASAGRC1)  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, gained for a third session, adding 5.2
percent to 18.35 soles after the central bank increased its
growth forecast for this year, said Inteligo SAB analyst Rodrigo Zuazo.  Telefonica del Peru SAA  (TELEFBC1 PE), the local unit of
Telefonica SA, gained 4.8 percent to 2.20 soles.  Austral Group SA (AUSTRAC1 PE), a unit of Austevoll Seafood
ASA, rose 3.4 percent to 30 centimos.  Grana y Montero SA  (GRAMONC1 PE), Peru’s largest
construction firm, climbed 2.5 percent to 8.35 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  